  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws targeting money laundering. These laws typically require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Implement customer due diligence procedures\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Conduct background checks\n5. Implement anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n\nIn the United States, key laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. Internationally, the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards for combating money laundering.\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution.",
